[normal]&#xa0;[bold]3.4.[bold]              [bold]What changes do workers demand?[bold]3.4.1
[normal]              
[normal]Workers were asked
[normal],
[normal] ‘What actions they thought UK Oil &amp; Gas must now take to improve safety?’ 
[normal] 
[normal]These questions involved changes 
[normal]workers would like to see made to the helicopter fleet and als
[normal]o
[normal] other methods for offshore transfers. Tellingly when asked about the use of both ships and fixed wing aircraft for offshore transfers a majority of the workforce did not support these options.
[normal] (Transfers by ship 41.5%, transfers by fixed wing aircraft 46.6%). 
[normal]3.4.2
[normal]              
[normal]When asked about changes to the helicopter fleet the most popular demand from the workforce is for a larger offshore fleet , 
[normal]supported by 
[normal]95.1% of workers, followed by c
[normal]hanges to th
[normal]e internal se
[normal]at configuration of helicopters
[normal], 
[normal]supported by 
[normal]92.9% of workers, followed by 
[normal]c
[normal]hanges to the design of helicopters used for passenger transport offshore
[normal], supported by
[normal] 92.2% of workers. 
[normal]3.4.3
[normal]              
[normal]These three actions are futher demonstrated as being 
[normal]the most important for the workforce as they were also the top three priorities when workers were asked to prioritise the actions that would
[normal] improve offshore flight safety.
[normal]What action(s) do you think the Oil &amp; Gas Industry must now take to improve offshor
[normal]e safety?
