[normal]Conclusion[bold]s[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]As a direct result of this consultation 
[normal]offshore workers on installations throughout the UKCS are taking an active role and supporting the 
[normal]‘Back Home Safe’
[normal] campaign.  
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Unite strongly believes the issues highlighted by 
[normal]the workers and the support for the four key demands emphasise 
[normal]the 
[normal]legitimate and genuine concerns among the workforce regarding 
[normal]the safety of 
[normal]helicopter transfers.  Both government and the wider industry have an obligation to address these concerns. 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In 
[normal]the same vein, there should be no surprise in either the industry or in government to the responses received via our consultation 
[normal]as 
[normal]these concerns have been growing and exacerbated with each major incident. 
[normal]The problem is further compounded when workers l
[normal]ook at their Norwegian counterparts and compare the respective safety records. 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.4.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The reality is that helicopter transfers are the most efficient, effective and in all likelihood, the safest means of commercial transfer to and from 
[normal]offshore installations. H
[normal]owever, that does not mean that changes to improve these transfers ca
[normal]nnot be undertaken immediately.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.5.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The oil and gas industry is our growth sector for the next thirty years but it is also at a crossroads as we move into what the industry refers to as the next phase of the UKCS. This is emphasised in the recently published Wood Review Interim Report, which
[normal] has recommended the fast-tracking of measures aimed at maximising the economic benefit of the remaining UK offshore capacity. 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.6.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]However, while the industry and government speed are at pains to maximise the remaining profits of the UKCS, this pursuit 
[normal]must 
[normal]be matched by an improved and robust health and safety agenda to protect the industry’s most important asset – its people. 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.7.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]As a result, Unite urges the committee to take on board these initial findings from our Back Home Safe Campaign as a highly represe
[normal]ntative sample of opinion from across the UK oil and gas workforce and help to address these clear concerns
[normal] with offshore helicopter safety with the utmost haste. 
